    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_CRIS_LoadCrisRawData",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to facilitate the loading of raw data into a SQL Server database by executing an SSIS (SQL Server Integration Services) package. The procedure performs several key tasks: it truncates specific tables to prepare them for new data, constructs a command to execute an SSIS package using "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "dtexec",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", and temporarily enables the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "xp_cmdshell",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " feature to run this command. The procedure is part of the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CrisNationalGridWest",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema within the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "OEC",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " database."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity of this stored procedure is considered medium due to the following factors:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "It involves multiple SQL operations, including table truncation and dynamic command execution."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "It requires enabling and disabling advanced SQL Server configuration options."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "It interacts with external systems through SSIS package execution, which adds an additional layer of complexity."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure does not explicitly define any input parameters. However, it is designed to execute an SSIS package with dynamically set variables for the database and server names."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "orderedList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Table Truncation",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure begins by truncating five tables ("
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "UploadAccountBillingDetailPreload",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "UploadBillingSummaryPreload",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "UploadExchangeDetailPreload",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "UploadMeterReadDetailPreload",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "UploadPaymentDetailPreload",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ") within the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "CrisNationalGridWest",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " schema. This step ensures that these tables are empty and ready to receive new data."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "SSIS Package Path Setup",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The path to the SSIS package ("
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Cris.dtsx",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ") is defined as a network path. This package is responsible for the data upload process."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Command Construction",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": A command string is constructed to execute the SSIS package using "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "dtexec",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". The command includes setting package variables for the database and server names dynamically using "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "DB_NAME()",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@@SERVERNAME",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Enable xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure temporarily enables the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " feature, which allows the execution of operating system commands from within SQL Server."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Execute SSIS Package",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The constructed command is executed using "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", which runs the SSIS package."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Disable xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": After executing the command, the procedure disables the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " feature to maintain security."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Truncation Overhead",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Truncating tables can be resource-intensive, especially if the tables are large. However, truncation is generally faster than deleting rows individually."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Network Latency",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The SSIS package is located on a network path, which may introduce latency or connectivity issues."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Command Execution",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Using "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " can be slow and may impact performance if the SSIS package execution takes a long time."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Potential Issues or Risks"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Security Risks",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Enabling "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " poses a security risk as it allows execution of arbitrary commands on the server. It should be used with caution and disabled when not in use."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Error Handling",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure lacks error handling mechanisms. If the SSIS package fails, there is no built-in way to capture or respond to the error."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Hardcoded Paths",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The SSIS package path is hardcoded, which may lead to issues if the path changes or if there are access permissions problems."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Concurrency",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": If multiple instances of this procedure are executed simultaneously, it could lead to conflicts or performance degradation due to table truncation and SSIS package execution."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "7. Stored Procedure Definition"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "codeBlock",
      "attrs": {
        "language": "sql"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CREATE PROCEDURE [CrisNationalGridWest].[usp_CRIS_LoadCrisRawData]\nAS\r\n--**************************************************************************************\r\n--* Name:         \r\n--*\r\n--* Description:  \r\n--*               \r\n--*               \r\n--*               \r\n--* Exec:         [CrisNationalGridWest].[usp_LoadCrisRawData]\r\n--*\r\n--* Parameter(s):         \r\n--*                            StatusCode  int output       \t   -  Execution Return Status \r\n--*\r\n--* Database:     OEC\r\n--*\r\n--* Return:\t    0 Success\r\n--*                   9 Failure\r\n--*\r\n--* AUTHOR:       Peter Heller (PAH)\r\n--* Created On:   10/17/2006\r\n--**************************************************************************************\r\n--* Date         Tech Description of Change\r\n--* ---------- ----  -------------------------------------------------------------\r\n--* 11/24/2009 PAH  First Version  \r\n--* 08/02/2013 DHO  Fully qualify path to dtexec\r\n--* Note the double quotes to perserve the spaces in the path name C:\\\"Program Files\"\\\"Microsoft SQL Server\"\\110\\DTS\\Binn\\dtexec\r\n--***************************************************************************************\r\nBegin \r\n\r\n\r\nDECLARE @ssispath VARCHAR(1000)\r\nDECLARE @cmd VARCHAR(1000)\r\n/**********************************************\r\nUpload ConEdison Raw Data\t\r\n**********************************************/\r\ntruncate table  CrisNationalGridWest.UploadAccountBillingDetailPreload\r\ntruncate table  CrisNationalGridWest.UploadBillingSummaryPreload\r\ntruncate table CrisNationalGridWest.UploadExchangeDetailPreload\r\ntruncate table CrisNationalGridWest.UploadMeterReadDetailPreload\r\ntruncate table CrisNationalGridWest.UploadPaymentDetailPreload\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSET @ssispath = '\\\\dcas.nycnet\\dfs\\shr_ec3_archive1$\\SSISpackage\\SSISDataUpload\\Cris.dtsx'\r\n--SET @cmd = 'C:\\\"Program Files\"\\\"Microsoft SQL Server\"\\110\\DTS\\Binn\\dtexec /f \"' + @ssispath + '\"' -- set ssis path\r\nSET @cmd = 'dtexec /f \"' + @ssispath + '\"' -- set ssis path\r\nSET @cmd = @cmd + ' /SET \\Package.Variables[User::DatabaseName].Properties[Value];\"' + DB_NAME() + '\"'\r\nSET @cmd = @cmd + ' /SET \\Package.Variables[User::ServerName].Properties[Value];\"' + @@SERVERNAME + '\"' \r\n\r\n\r\nEXEC sp_configure 'show advanced options', 1\r\nRECONFIGURE\r\nEXEC sp_configure 'xp_cmdshell', 1\r\nRECONFIGURE\r\nEXEC xp_cmdshell @cmd\r\n\r\n--EXEC xp_cmdshell @cmd\r\n\r\nEXEC sp_configure 'show advanced options', 1\r\nRECONFIGURE\r\nEXEC sp_configure 'xp_cmdshell', 0\r\nRECONFIGURE\r\n\r\n\r\nEND"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}